text: Panoramic view of Salobre Salobre is a town and municipality in the province of Albacete, Spain. It also contains the small village of Reolid. In 2017, the municipality had a population of 523 inhabitants, according to statistics released by the National Statistics Institute of Spain. The inhabitants are distributed between the village of Reolid, with 173 inhabitants, and the town of Salobre, with 350 inhabitants. ==References== Category:Municipalities of the Province of Albacete
title: Salobre
